["Kirkcaldy Burghs was a burgh constituency of the House of Commons of the Parliament of the United Kingdom (Westminster) from 1832 to 1974. It elected one Member of Parliament (MP) by the first-past-the-post voting system. From 1832 to 1950 it was, officially, a district of burghs constituency.","Comprising Kirkcaldy, Burntisland, Dysart, Kinghorn and the Municipal Borough of Kirkcaldy not included in the old Parliamentary Borough (except that portion within the Parliamentary Borough of Dysart).[2]","The burghs of Kirkcaldy, Buckhaven, Methil and Innerleven, Burntisland, Dysart and Kinghorn."]